author: COMSOL
description: This tutorial model demonstrates electrodeposition of a nickel-phosphorous alloy. The model accounts for charge and mass transport of a multitude of species along with multiple electrode reactions such as nickel and phosphorus electrodeposition and hydrogen evolution. The model computes the steady state spatial distributions of the various species along the diffusion layer. The polarization plot along with deposition mole fraction plot reveal the desirable operating conditions for alloy preparation.
